<br>
&quot;Wizards right now have two specialties, damage and teleportation. They should be the masters of arcane magic and ripping holes in the fabric of space. Making them the masters of teleportation not only makes a lot of sense, it also adds a dimension to the class.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, we are moving toward making Wizards the master of arcane transportation. This seems like the right direction to take the class.&quot; <br>
<br>
Alan <br>
<br>
Now my argument...<br>
<br>
Didn't VI say a while back that druids were the masters of transportation?  I thought that was the explanation for them getting nicer and earlier lvl teleport spells.  That's also why they have Spirit of Wolf, remember?  Certainly not to allow them to kite.  And don't forget traveling utilities: Enduring breath, levitate, invisibility (camo, whatever).. even wolf form for faction certain places!<br>
<br>
So if druids are no longer masters of traveling, doesn't that mean they don't need all these spells anymore?  I personally think that if wizards are now the masters of transportation, then we should be able to run faster than others, and have all those other abilities earlier than druids.<br>
<br>
I'm not one to scream for other classes to be nerfed, so our SoW should be faster than druid, shaman, or bards could ever hope to run <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And our version of wolf from (I like drake form myself) should have good faction everywhere and provide super running speed, mana regen, night vision, levitate, underwater breathing, and an in-flight movie. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Finally, wizards should have a teleport to every single zone in the game (dungeons included).  And the first gates should be at lvl 12, not 20.  Portals at 16.  And evacs/translocates at 20.<br>
<br>
If all these things are given to wizards, then the new description really would be a fix (kinda), otherwise, it is a pimp smack in the nuts.<br>
